# JIT Transcoding API Service
Just-in-time video transcoding service that exposes the JitTranscoder through REST API endpoints for real-time video streaming with multiple quality options.

## Test plan / verification steps
```bash
# Start the JIT transcoding service
cd services/jit-transcoding
npm run dev

# Run the test suite
npm test

# Run integration tests specifically
npm run test:integration

# Manual testing (optional)
curl http://localhost:3001/health
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/v1/transcode/low?url=https://example.com/video.mp4&start=0" -o segment_low.mp4
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/v1/transcode/medium?url=https://example.com/video.mp4&start=2000" -o segment_medium.mp4
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/v1/transcode/high?url=https://example.com/video.mp4&start=4000" -o segment_high.mp4

# Test error handling (should return 400)
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/v1/transcode/custom?url=https://example.com/video.mp4&start=0" # Invalid preset
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/v1/transcode/low?url=https://example.com/video.mp4&start=1500" # Not 2s aligned
```

